	<h2><code>DEFINE SCOPE</code> statement</h2>
	<p>
		Setting scope access allows SurrealDB to operate as a web database. With scopes you can set authentication and access rules which enable fine-grained access to tables and fields.
	</p>
	<Docs::Heading @level="4" @id="requirements">Requirements</Docs::Heading>
	<ul>
		<li>To use<code>DEFINE SCOPE</code> you must have root, namespace, or database level access.</li>
		<li><LinkTo @route="docs.surrealql.statements.use">You must select your namespace and database</LinkTo> before you can use the <code>DEFINE SCOPE</code> statement.</li>
	</ul>
</Layout::Text>

